  Setup  A Nuxt module for simplifying the use of Mongoose in your project.  Installation   Install   nuxt-mongoose  to your dependencies.     npx   nuxi@latest   module   add   nuxt-mongoose
   Add   nuxt-mongoose  to the   modules  section of your   nuxt.config  file.     export   default   defineNuxtConfig  ({
     modules: [
       'nuxt-mongoose'  ,
     ],
   })
   That's it! You can now use Mongoose in your Nuxt app âœ¨  Options  You can configure the module by adding a   mongoose  section to your   nuxt.config  file.
read more about   Mongoose options .     export   default   defineNuxtConfig  ({
     mongoose: {
       // Options
     },
   })
  If you want to configure only the   uri  just add   MONGODB_URI  in your   .env  file.   MONGODB_URI=YOUR_MONGO_URI
